  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with clinical diagnosis of E.T. for at least a year by a movement disorder
             neurologist

          -  A +2 or worse action or kinetic tremor of one or both upper limbs involving at least
             the forearm and/or hand

          -  Ages 18 to 95 years old

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  (+) sensory loss in the upper extremities

          -  dermatologic lesions in upper extremities (e.g. skin cancer, eczema, fresh or healing
             wounds, abrasions, acne, pustules, abscesses, or skin rash)

          -  known history of sensitivity to cold (i.e., cold urticaria)

          -  known peripheral vascular disease

          -  Raynaud's phenomenon

          -  scleroderma
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
